Add $38+2$ then add $33$.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{38}+\purpleD{36}&=\blueE{38}+\purpleD{2}+\purpleD{34}\\\\
&\neq \blueE{38}+\purpleD{2}+\redE{33}
\end{align}$

**No**, this strategy does **not** work.

Add $30+30$ then add $8$ then add $6$.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{38}+\purpleD{36}&=\blueE{30}+\blueE{8}+\purpleD{30}+\purpleD6\\\\
&= \blueE{30}+\purpleD{30}+\blueE{8}+\purpleD{6}
\end{align}$

**Yes**, this strategy works.
